					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, you need to keep your target system in mind. At least the case of running several instances is embarrassingly parallel though, so if your emulator is single-threaded you can scale it up to at least the number of available cores (just experimented with 10 or so instances, and they ran fine until X11 decided to crash <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />).<br /><br />Guess issues like memory contention might come in too, but seemed to work fine in practice in this case. Prolly shouldn't have a huge cache footprint...</div>

