					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The ability to apply Moore's law to raw cpu speed has long since disappeared. Transistors density and count has continued to rise, and even get more efficient, but algorithmic improvements are far more effective at saving power than just waiting for Intel to fix it for you. Don't throw away an optimized version unless it's getting in the way of correctness.<br /><br />TL;DR: Targeting a device with a battery? You darn well better optimize.</div>

